===message:It's always been interesting to me that Southern states contend that they fought the Civil War for "states' rights" rather than for the institution of slavery. Even our textbooks made sure that we were all clear on that. As a Southerner, I think we need to look at our past more honestly and accept responsibility for who we've been. Wouldn't our stance on states' rights have been discussed righteously on the front porch while slaves served us lemonade? It seems like a bizarre denial to me.
